raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "Hapi" %}
{% set version = "1.2.3" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://github.com/MAfarrag/Hapi/archive/{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: c3c027f48f0a23eba0dc7b881c053ca036ddd5cacebff6ea33e5a07d4099e847

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:

  host:
    - python >=3.7
    - pip
  run:
    - pip>=21.3.1
    - numpy>=1.21.2,<1.22.4
    - gdal==3.4.0
    - affine==2.3.0
    - fiona==1.8.20
    - pyproj>=3.2.1,<=3.3.0
    - pandas>=1.3.2,<1.4.3
    - Rtree>=0.9.4
    - geopandas>=0.10.2
    - matplotlib>=3.4.2,<3.6.0
    - scipy>=1.7.0,<1.8.1
    - shapely>=1.8.0
    - statsmodels>=0.12.2,<0.14.0
    - rasterio>=1.2.10
    - rasterstats>=0.16.0
    - oasis>=1.0.2
    - netCDF4>=1.5.5,<1.5.9
    - scikit-image>=0.18.3
    - scikit-learn>=0.24.2,<1.0.3
    - ecmwf-api-client>=1.6.1
    - joblib>=1.1.0
    - geopy>=2.2.0
    - loguru>=0.5.3
    - geoplot>=0.5.1
    - pytest-cov>=2.12.1
    - pytest>=6.2.5
test:
  imports:
    - Hapi

about:
  home: https://github.com/MAfarrag/HAPI
  license: BSD-3-Clause
  license_file: LICENSE.md
  license_family: BSD
  license_file: LICENSE.md
  summary: Distributed Hydrological model
  description: |
    This module builds Distributed Hydrological model.
  dev_url: https://github.com/MAfarrag/HAPI
  doc_url: https://hapi-hm.readthedocs.io/
  doc_source_url: https://github.com/MAfarrag/HAPI/master/README.md

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - MAfarrag
